2 cents for me is that non-contributors might not would want to open DEVELOPER.md so maybe better to move only `report a bug` section to README, and keep other sections.

@Ethanlm 
Thanks for the update. I'll try to get it today and put my observation.
Btw, my additional commits didn't address anything about bug fix so it doesn't matter which commit you're testing with.

@HeartSaVioR I have not tested on a secure cluster at all.  It was all on a single node cluster.

I verified that as many links as I could worked correctly.  I verified I could switch between files, search through files.  I verified that log files were cleaned up as expected as the size grew.

The only other thing that I just noticed is that the pull down for selecting files does not have the current file selected as the default.  (again this can probably be done in a follow on JIRA)
